modules.description: This module provides low-level, high-performance operations for creating, manipulating, and converting bigstrings with direct byte-level access, including unsafe memory reads/writes and endianness-aware integer serialization. It operates on `Bigstringaf.t` (Bigarray-based bigstrings), `string`, `Bytes.t`, and other string-like types, enabling efficient binary data processing, buffer management, and zero-copy interoperability. Specific use cases include high-speed binary protocol parsing, memory-mapped I/O, and performance-critical applications requiring precise control over memory layout and data representation.
